2,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T05:19:01.000Z","msg":"請問 ching, 如果人在英國，控制香港 IB Account 買美股，咁駛唔駛俾英國政府收 Capital gain tax?<br />\n如果收，係計賣出咗嘅股票所賺嘅錢去計？定係每年報稅時 re-value 咁計？係會自己報稅時報咁？<br />\n<br />\n多謝解答。"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T05:23:36.000Z","msg":"不過人在英國 tax status 都可以係 non-resident"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T05:25:05.000Z","msg":"住唔夠半年？"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T05:27:35.000Z","msg":"Whether you&rsquo;re UK resident usually depends on how many days you spend in the UK in the tax year (6 April to 5 April the following year).<br />\nYou&rsquo;re automatically resident if either:<br />\nyou spent 183 or more days in the UK in the tax year<br />\nyour only home was in the UK - you must have owned, rented or lived in it for at least 91 days in total - and you spent at least 30 days there in the tax year<br />\nYou&rsquo;re automatically non-resident if either:<br />\nyou spent fewer than 16 days in the UK (or 46 days if you have not been classed as UK resident for the 3 previous tax years)<br />\nyou work abroad full-time (averaging at least 35 hours a week) and spent fewer than 91 days in the UK, of which no more than 30 were spent working<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/tax-foreign-income/residence\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Ftax-foreign-income%2Fresidence&d=mfTbPTXtdXcWugdQC%2B6BDlQYB6qXEwX4CB7r1YlVkGU%3D&h=59c57fe7\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/tax-foreign-income/residence</a>"},{"pid":"32613010d04305e7a6de7aec6a48fd64d20523eb","tid":2174724,"uid":255976,"like":1,"dislike":2,"score":-1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T06:27:45.000Z","msg":"我個人答案是要交稅。<br />\n英國比BNO入去，正正經經交稅是必要的。"},{"pid":"950d30ffeb5330dea2e64f9754b11b37c700a3b4","tid":2174724,"uid":194298,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-26T06:35:07.000Z","msg":"有免稅額，除非你玩好大..<br />\n不過報就照報左先，交未必駛交既"},{"pid":"4bc02ae5296e8014399dbc5beb43962480bfeb6c","tid":2174724,"uid":217817,"like":1,"d